        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#aboutAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-body">
            Seven authentic survivor letters form the heart of the narrative. Each voice represents a distinct perspective:<br>
            - Jonas Hutchinson (lawyer): institutional collapse<br>
            - Mary Fales (lawyer’s wife): family displacement<br>
            - George Howland (school principal): loss of knowledge<br>
            - Aurelia R. King (merchant’s family): survival and faith<br>
            - Anna E. Higginson (broker’s wife): preservation consciousness<br>
            - Adeline Rossiter Judd (volunteer): mutual aid<br>
            - Samuel Stone (assistant librarian): vision for rebuilding[attached_file:10].
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Card 3: Geographic Specificity -->
